msIdentifier.collection: John Frederick Lewis Collection of European Manuscripts

msContents.summary: This manuscript contains a late thirteenth-century copy of the Organon and related texts.

msItem.title: Leaf from liturgical manuscript [breviary?], 11th or early 12th century
Porphyry, Isagoge in Aristotelis Praedicamenta (Introduction to Aristotle's Categories)
msItem.incipit: Cum sit necessariu[m] g[ri]saurolus [?] et ad ea[m] q[uae] e[st] ap[ud] ari[stotelem] p[rae]dicam[en]tor[um] doct[ri]na[m] nossce q[uid] sit g[enus]
msItem.explicit: S[un]t a[u]t[em] ali[a]e q[uid] co[mm]itates u[e]l p[rop]rietes eor[um] q[uae] d[i]c[t]a s[unt] s[ed] sufficia[n]t h[aec] e[tiam] ad dis[tin]ct[i]o[n]em eor[um] c[ommuni]tatis et t[ra]dit[i]o[n]em. d[e]o g[ratias] am[en]. [Fol. 8r]

msItem.title: Aristotle Liber Praedicamenta (Catagories)
msItem.incipit: [A]Equiuoca d[ici]n[tu]r quor[um] solu[m] co[mmun]e e[st] s[ecundum] u[er]o nom[en]
msItem.explicit: Forte t[amen] et alii q[ui]da[m] appareb[un]t modi de eo q[uod] e[st] h[abere]s[ed] q[ui] [con]sueruer[un]t dici p[a]ene o[mn]es enu[mer]ati su[n]t. Deo gra[tia]s am[en] am[en] am[en]. [fol. 21v]

msItem.title: Aristotle, De interpretatione (On interpretation)
msItem.incipit: Primum oportet [con]stituere q[uid] sit nom[en] et q[uid] u[er]bu[m] et postea q[uid] neg[atio] et q[uid] affir[m]atio
msItem.explicit: si[mu]l eni[m] eide[m] no[n] [con]ti[n]git e[ss]e [contrar]ia. d[e]o gra[tia]s. [fol. 29r]

msItem.title: Gilbertus Porretanus, Liber sex principioum
msItem.incipit: Forma est [com]po[sition]i [con]ti[n]ge[n]s si[m]plici et i[n]uariab[i]li e[ss]entia [con]siste[n]s
msItem.explicit: et h[aec] d[e] sex p[ri]n[cipi]us d[o]c[trin]a[m] sufficia[n]t deo gratias. [fol. 35v]

msItem.title: Aristotle, Analytica priora (Prior Analytics)
msItem.incipit: Primum o[portet] dice[re] c[ir]ca q[uid] et d[e] q[uo] est [in]te[n]tio
msItem.explicit: si a[utem] n[on] no[n] e[r]it unu[m] ini[us] signu[m]. Deo gra[ti]as am[en] am[en] ame[n]. [fol. 75v]

msItem.title: Aristotle, Analytica posteriora (Posterior Analytics)
msItem.incipit: Omnis doctrina et o[mn]is dissciplina i[n]t[e]llect[iv]a ex p[re]hesiste[n]ti cog[ni]t[i]o[n]e fit
msItem.explicit: h[oc] a[utem] e[sse] si[mi]l[ite]r se h[abe]nt ad r[ati]o[n]em {?} rer[um].

msItem.title: Aristotle, Topica (Topics)
msItem.incipit: Propositum q[ui]d[e]m negotii e[st] methodum inuenire
msItem.explicit: In prohemio alia t[ame]n statio In laudes u[niuersa]liu[m] p[ro]positu[m] t[er]minat R[?] tractatu[m]. [Fol. 159r]

msItem.title: Aristotle, De Sophisticis Elenchis (On Sophistical Refutation)
msItem.incipit: De sophisticis autem elencis et de his q[ui] uident[ur] q[ui]dem elenci s[ed] no[n] elenci su[n]t
msItem.explicit: opus onus si a[utem] artis indulsia[ne]m Inuenictis{?} a[u]t[em] multas h[abe]re grates am[en] am[en] am[en]. [Fol. 177v]

supportDesc.extent: ii+178+i; 280 x 198 mm bound to 290 x 208 mm
supportDesc.foliation: The first four leaves of each quire are numbered with an alphabetical letter and Arabic numeral; modern foliation in pencil upper right recto; contemporary running heads top center margin

p.catchwords: Horizontal lower inner margin verso; some catchwords surrounded by decorated frames lower center margin; fols. 51, 59, 67, 75, 83, 91, 111, 119, 127, 135, 143, 151, 161, 170

layoutDesc.layout: Ruled in lead point and ink in one column of 26 lines; written area: 147 x 112 mm; the work of several scribes; fol. 103 is blank; fol. 178 is blank and ruled; the first flyleaf, possibly bound with the original manuscript, contains two columns of twenty-five lines of text, hard point ruling, cut off at the bottom; on the verso are six lines of so-called "Nonantulan Notation," used, according to Wolf, at Nonantula, near Modena; pricking is visible along the right edge; on the recto, the leaf is numbered 203, with "June 1818" in the upper right corner

decoDesc.decoNote: Twenty decorated initials with foliate extensions of varying lengths begin new books and chapters; fol. 35v features a figured initial by a different artist, with a human figure surrounded by grotesques; charts appear throughout decorated in red and black; annotations and manicules appear throughout; running heads in red identify the various books; paraph markers alternate in blue and red, with occasional flourished initials beginning sections
Inside front coverBookplate, John Frederick Lewis

binding.p: Late nineteenth-century half red straight grain morocco; stamped in gold on spine: "Isagogi of Porphory. Latin MS. XIV [Cent.].","No. 203 in a London sale, June 1818 [per De Ricci]; Preston A. Perry sale, New York, April 21, 1908, no. 263; John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936

history.provenance: No. 203 in a London sale, June 1818 [per De Ricci]; Preston A. Perry sale, New York, April 21, 1908, no. 263; John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936; In the front flyleaf is the bookmark of J. F. Lewis, with notes written above: "Italian, very early 14th century Aristotle: Organon Preceding leaf probably 11th century."; attached to f. 178r is the auction catalogue description for lot 263
